-- India Companies May Report 1.9% Higher Profit in Three Months to June 30
-- Paresh Jatakia
-- 2010-07-12T10:52:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/india-companies-may-report-1-9-higher-profit-in-three-months-to-june-30.html

          
          
             The following are the mean of analystsâ€™ forecasts
for profit and sales compiled by Bloomberg for the 30 companies in the benchmark
Bombay Stock Exchange  Sensitive Index  for the quarter ended June 30. The
forecasts show companies on average will report 1.91 percent higher profit in
the quarter from a year earlier.  
 Company names are in alphabetical order and figures are in billions of
rupees (1 billion rupees = $21.4 million). The estimates are based on figures
submitted by analysts. Actual profit and sales declared in the quarter is shown
in the middle column. Company tickers and time periods are listed in brackets.  

 

